HEADWORD: Merlon
<hw>Mer"lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., perh. fr. L.
<ets>moerus</ets>, for <ets>murus</ets> a wall, through (assumed) dim.
<ets>moerulus</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>One of the solid
parts of a battlemented parapet; a battlement. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Battlement</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Merluce</ent>⟦br⟧
